Git - Git is a free, distributed version control system, that helps track and manage changes in code over time. 
It allow multiple developers to work on the same project, view previous version, and restore changes when needed.
Git is the version control system, it help track and manage the code, it provide CLI to interact with git

GitHub- it is platform which is used for the same and some extra functionalities 
It is used for source code management. Here we have the GUI


Other similar tools- bitbucket well suited with jira nd CI/CD
Gitlab well suited with CI/CD and AI
Github well suited for copilot github actions



Features of Git
1- Version Control System- Git keep track of every changes we make to our project files, we can back to previous version if required.

2- Repositories- A Git repositories is like a project central hub where everything related to the project is stored and managed
There are 2 type of Repositories:
Local Repo- This is the copy of the central repo which is stored in the computer, we can work on our project and make the changes here.
Remote Repo- This is the main or can say central repo which is stored on server like GitHub, here we and other can share the code and work on the project.

3- Commit- Every time we make change and save in the git that is called commit , the repo keep track off the commit we have made.

4- Branches- A Repo allow us to create the branch and work on the new feature and fixes,
Ex- we have a main branch for the stable code, and feature branch for the new feature we are developing.

5- Merging- Once we have done the work on the branches we have made then we can merge those branches into main branch.
This adds the changes we made in the project.

6- Cloning- Cloning is the process of making a complete copy of git repository, it’s like copying the entire project from the central local to our computer.

Advantage of using Git
Distributed System- Every developer have complete project copy to their system which allow developer’s to work offline.
Performance- Git is fast and efficient, handle large project with ease.
Branching & Merging- Git provide the lightweight branching and easy merging facility which allow parallel development and feature isolation.
Collaboration- Tools like GitHub enhance team collaboration, code review and project management.
Track Changes- Git tracks changes and maintain a history, which makes easy to revert to previous version.

