 Basic Git Commands
Git init: Initializes a new git repo
git init

Git rm –cached <filename>: this command is used to unstaged the staged file after running git add . 
git rm --cached <filename>

Git restore <filename>: to recover deleted file
git restore <filename>
Git Clone: Clone a remote repository to our local system
Note- this download the entire project file to the local system
git clone [URL]

Git add : It stages the changes to be committed 
git add .
Or 
git add <filename>

Git commit -m : this command commit the stages changes with a msg.
git commit -m "comment msg"

Git push : this command pushes the commit to the remote repo/central repo.
git push origin <branch name>

Git pull : This command fetch and merge the changes from the remote repo to the local repo.
git pull origin <branch name>

Git Status: Shows the status of changes in the working director.
git status


Drawbacks: Branch merging conflicts are challenging to resolve.

Advance Concept of Git
Branching: 
1- Check Current Branch:
git status

2- Check local branches: 
git branch

3- Check remote branches:
git branch -r

4- Check All branches(remote and local):
git branch -a

5- Create Branch:
git branch feature1

6- Rename current branch:
git branch -m <new-name>

7- Rename another branch:
git branch -m <old-name> <new-name>

8- Switch Branch:
git checkout feature1
Or
git switch feature1

9- Create + Switch Branch:
git checkout -b feature2
Or
git switch -c feature

10- Merge Branch:
git checkout main
git merge feature1

11- Delete a Branch: 
git branch -d <branch-name>
For force delete-
git branch -D <branch-name>

12- Compare Branch:
git diff <main-branch> <feature-branch>

13- See Merged Branch:
git branch --merged

14- See Un-Merged Branch:
git branch --no-merged

15-  Push a branch to remote:
git push origin <branch-name>

16- Delete a remote branch:
git push origin --delete <branch-name>

17- Fetch all remote branch: Download branch info from remote
git fetch --all

18- Find which branch contains a commit:
git branch --contains <commit-id>

19- Push all local Branches:
git push --all origin

Connect Git to GitHub:
Step1- Create a repo in github
Step2- Connect github repo to the local git 
git remote add origin <repo-url>

Step3- Verify the connection 
git remote -v

Step4- Push file to remote repo
git push -u origin main
Push- upload commits
Origin- github repo
-u - remember this connection for future push and pull 
Main- branch name from the branch we want to push the file
Important Commands:
1- Change Github Repo URL: to configure any other remote repo locally 
Ex- currently we have added remote origin - anant-linux-repo but now you want to change this origin to any other github repo like to- anant-git-note-repo
git remote set-url origin <new-repo-url>

2- Remove Github Connection:
git remote remove origin
Or 
git remote rm origin

Other Impt command after connecting git and github:
1- Clone an existing repository: it downloads all the project files from remote repo to local computer
git clone <repo-url>

2- Push a complete new branch to github:
git push origin <branch-name>

3- Download and merge changes from github:
git pull origin master

4- To push from local master branch to github master branch
git push origin master:master
Or
git push origin master
Or
git push
Or 
git push -u origin master

5- To push from local login-feature branch to remote repo master branch
